  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: Package binds two requirements whose acceptance thresholds are mutually exclusive at the nominal operating point (6 L/min, 3500 RPM): REQ-HEM-01 mandates RH < 1.0 relative to the predicate device for all evaluated flow-speed combinations, while REQ-HEM-02 mandates RH ≤ 1.05 as the minimum acceptable threshold and explicitly permits values in the range 1.00 < RH ≤ 1.05 as compliant — directly contradicting REQ-HEM-01's prohibition of any RH ≥ 1.0.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/hem-01-strict",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
