    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 requirements. CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Validation against FDA benchmark dataset shows mean absolute error of 8.3%, within the ±15% acceptance criterion. Package accepted for regulatory submission support. Note: The credibility team reviewed both REQ-HEM-01 (RH < 1.0 strictly) and REQ-HEM-02 (RH ≤ 1.05 with explicit allowance for 1.00 < RH ≤ 1.05) and considered them jointly satisfied; the tension between these requirements at the 6 L/min / 3500 RPM operating point (CFD RH = 1.02) was not flagged as a non-conformance.",
